@endpoint GET /subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.Sql/managedInstances/{managedInstanceName}/databases/{databaseName}/securityAlertPolicies/{securityAlertPolicyName}
@desc Gets a managed database's security alert policy.
@required {resourceGroupName: any # The name of the resource group that contains the resource. You can obtain this value from the Azure Resource Manager API or the portal., managedInstanceName: any # The name of the managed instance., databaseName: any # The name of the managed database for which the security alert policy is defined., securityAlertPolicyName: any # The name of the security alert policy., subscriptionId: any # The subscription ID that identifies an Azure subscription., api-version: any # The API version to use for the request.}
@returns(200) Successfully retrieved the managed database security alert policy.

@endpoint PUT /subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.Sql/managedInstances/{managedInstanceName}/databases/{databaseName}/securityAlertPolicies/{securityAlertPolicyName}
@desc Creates or updates a database's security alert policy.
@required {resourceGroupName: any # The name of the resource group that contains the resource. You can obtain this value from the Azure Resource Manager API or the portal., managedInstanceName: any # The name of the managed instance., databaseName: any # The name of the managed database for which the security alert policy is defined., securityAlertPolicyName: any # The name of the security alert policy., parameters: map # The database security alert policy., subscriptionId: any # The subscription ID that identifies an Azure subscription., api-version: any # The API version to use for the request.}
@returns(200) Successfully set the managed database security alert policy.
@returns(201) Successfully created the managed database security alert policy.

@endpoint GET /subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.Sql/managedInstances/{managedInstanceName}/databases/{databaseName}/securityAlertPolicies
@desc Gets a list of managed database's security alert policies.
@required {resourceGroupName: any # The name of the resource group that contains the resource. You can obtain this value from the Azure Resource Manager API or the portal., managedInstanceName: any # The name of the managed instance., databaseName: any # The name of the managed database for which the security alert policies are defined., subscriptionId: any # The subscription ID that identifies an Azure subscription., api-version: any # The API version to use for the request.}
